{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"15921811-f17b-463a-8d3d-a35a5473afa1","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**`.csproj` changes:**\n1. **Target framework**: MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+; upgrade from `net462`\n2. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n3. **Replace** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the single `MSTest` v3 meta-package (it bundles the test SDK, framework, and adapter)\n\n**Test code**: No changes needed — MSTest v3 is backward-compatible with `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`, etc.\n\nWant me to apply these changes? The updated `.csproj` would look like:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c6ff03f0-5e04-4502-bddd-90fdec86bb9f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the current state. The project:\n\n1. Targets `net462` (.NET Framework)\n2. References `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` via assembly reference (the old way)\n3. Has `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0\n4. Uses `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, I need to:\n\n1. Remove the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. Add the `MSTest` NuGet package (v3.x) — MSTest v3 consolidated the packages into a single `MSTest` package\n\n\n3. There's a critical issue though: MSTest v3 dropped .NET Framework support entirely and requires .NET 6.0 or later, so the user would need to retarget the project to a newer framework.\n\nLet me verify the exact compatibility requirements. MSTest v3 supports .NET 6.0+ and possibly .NET 8.0+ depending on the specific version, but definitely no longer supports .NET Frame